HEADWORD: Noble-minded
<hw>No"ble-mind`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a noble
mind; of high moral or intellectual character; honorable;
magnanimous.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>No"ble-mind`ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> exalted, high-flown, high-minded, lofty,
idealistic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>noble-mindedness</ent>⟦br⟧
